# SignalsConf Berlin PC Briefing

Date: Mar 17, 2026  
Author: [Heinrich Hartmann](mailto:hhartmann.1729@gmail.com)

# Mission & Positioning

With the AI revolution in full swing, many long-standing assumptions and best practices in software development and operations are being challenged. New interaction patterns, new system architectures, and rapidly evolving development workflows are changing how software systems are built, deployed, and operated.

Signals Berlin exists to create a space where experienced practitioners and leaders in the field can come together to examine these changes and share what they are seeing in real systems. The goal is to surface lessons and emerging patterns from production, experiments, failures, emerging patterns, and unresolved questions, and to help the community collectively make sense of a rapidly evolving landscape.

## Principles

**Humility, Transparency, Integrity.** Signals encourages honest accounts of real operational experience. Not everything works, and many of the most valuable lessons come from things that fail or fall apart in unexpected ways. We explicitly welcome talks that share failed experiments, surprising outcomes, and unresolved challenges. Learning from what did not work is often as valuable as showcasing what did.

**Solve for Hallway Quality.** The quality of the conference will not be measured primarily by the quality of the talks, but by the quality of the Hallway discussions that happen around them. The program is designed to bring together a highly relevant group of participants and give them the time and space to exchange ideas.

**Share early thinking.** Signals is a place where we share work and ideas that are still in progress. This can include, emerging ideas or operational principles, early experimental results, trends supported by real data points. Talks do not need to present finished frameworks or polished narratives. Often the most valuable contributions come from people sharing what problems they see, which principles they arrived at, and which solution strategies they are trying. 

